__PrivCrochet_tags: 
title: Safety
---
<<declare $safetyVisited = 0>>
<<if $safetyVisited==0>>
    SHC Officer: Hold up, Mel. B. 
    SHC Officer: You've been randomly selected for an occupational compliance and safety inspection. 
    Melion Bisclavret: Please move. 
    SHC Officer: Don't be so cold hearted, Mel. B. S'just protocol.
    Melion Bisclavret: I really, *really* do not have time for this.
    SHC Officer: That's what you said last week. 
    SHC Officer: Someone's gotta be concerned for your well-being. 
    SHC Officer: Might as well be me. We're here to make sure that blade of yours is up to code.
    Melion Bisclavret: Who is 'we'? It's always just you.
    SHC Officer: I'm loyal like that.
    SHC Officer: There's quite a commotion on the upper floors. Seems everyone's brandishing something or other. It's like they're preparing for war.
    SHC Officer: So I rushed down here. Us little guys oughta' stick together, huh?
    -> Yes.
        Melion Bisclavret: Sure.
        SHC Officer: Right on, Mel. B.
    -> No.
        Melion Bisclavret: No.
        SHC Officer: Agree to disagree, Mel. B. 
    SHC Officer: Anyway, would you like to start a brief safety training refresher?
    -> No.
        Melion Bisclavret: No.
    -> No.
        Melion Bisclavret: No.
    SHC Officer: Too bad. 'S mandatory.  
    SHC Officer: If you find yourself in a duel with a fellow employee, try to resolve the situation through dialogue. It might not always work out the way you expect, though.
    SHC Officer: Getting into the headspace of your opponent can give you hints about their next move. If they seem focused on you, it could mean an attack is imminent.
    SHC Officer: In that case, ready yourself and prepare to block. But if they seem distracted, take it as a sign to strike.
    SHC Officer: Hypothetically speaking, of course. You should always resolve conflicts non-violently.
    SHC Officer: Anyway, it looks like your sword is up to code. I'll get out of your way now.
    <<set $safetyIsCollidable = 0 >>
    Melion Bisclavret: Thank the lord.
    SHC Officer: Buuuuut if you have any more questions, you can always come back to me for help. Your saftey is our number one priority.
    SHC Officer: I'll be '[Z]'ing you.
    <<set $safetyVisited = 1 >>

<<elseif $safetyVisited == 1>>
    SHC Officer: You're back for more tips? 
    SHC Officer: I got a whole booklet of em right here. You can have it, they give us extras at the branch HQ.
    Bisclavret reluctatntly obtained a copy of 'Clarification of SHC1910.212 and SHC1910.242, as applying to hand-type office paper cutters and sharp edged hand tools'.
    Bisclavret discretely disposed of the booklet in a nearby waste bin.
    << set $gotBooklet = 1>>
    Melion Bisclavret: Thanks.
    SHC Officer: Good luck, Mel. B. It's a spicy world up there.
    <<set $safetyVisited = 2 >>
<<elseif $safetyVisited > 1>>
    <<if $gotBooklet == 2>>
        An unknown force compels Bisclavret on this pointless errand.
        Melion Bisclavret: Is the SHC going paperless?
        SHC Officer: Not that I heard, Mel. B. 
        SHC Officer: But if we are, I'll be sure to hand em all off to you.
        Melion Bisclavret: Lovely.
        << set $gotBooklet = 3>>
    <<endif>>
    SHC Officer: Sorry, Mel. B. I'm out of pamphlets. I'll have more for you next week.
    Melion Bisclavret: Next week? What happened to 'randomly selected'?
    SHC Officer: I'll just randomly select you again? Simple as.
<<endif>>
